column3:
Looks like there have been some changes since you opened this.

Please pick up the latest changes, then replace the wiki page with a message, so no more edits are done there.

I'll merge this tomorrow, before tagging -final.
Have pulled in the final changes and closed editing in the wiki.

ACK 8bca3ce0b121b77bec4915617dfceed4c023962c\n\nI'm going to move forward with this, there's been plenty of time to make edits on the wiki, or comment on one of the issues related with 0.19. We don't tend to hold up releases on release notes.
Shouldn't we mention #16714 here?\nIt is a really notable change for bitcoin-qt users.

Gui users will either see the intro screen and the new feature, because it is a fresh install. Or they don't, because it is not a fresh install. In either case it wouldn't help them if they knew about it upfront. Also, at some point we need to pull the release notes and push out the release.
